curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/3235' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM44603", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM44603 is a quad, SPDT (single-pole/double-  throw), TTL/CMOS compatible analog switch. It  operates from a 1.8V to 5.5V single power supply.  The SGM44603 features high-speed, low on-resistance,  low voltage and high bandwidth. The high performances  make it very suitable for multiple applications, such as  portable equipment, audio and video signal routing, etc.  Low power consumption is also one of the important  reasons that make it a good choice.  The SGM44603 is available in a Green TQFN-  2.6×1.8-16L package. It operates over an ambient  temperature range of -40℃ to +85℃.        "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/3236' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM44603", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● Single Supply Voltage Range: 1.8V to 5.5V  ● -3dB Bandwidth: 300MHz  ● Low On-Resistance: 4.5Ω (TYP) at 5V  ● Low On-Resistance Flatness  ● High Off-Isolation: -70dB at 1MHz  ● Low Crosstalk: -90dB at 1MHz  ● Fast Switching Times:  tON: 40ns  tOFF: 30ns  ● Rail-to-Rail Input and Output Operation  ● Low Power Consumption  ● TTL/CMOS Compatible  ● -40℃ to +85℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in a Green TQFN-2.6×1.8-16L Package      "}'
